# Backend Layer Separation

## Routers

- Parse HTTP input, call a service, return a response or raise HTTPException.
- No database `Session`, no SQL queries, no business rules in route handlers.
- Use `Depends()` for auth, pagination, and service injection.

## Services

- Own business logic and transaction boundaries.
- Accept primitives or Pydantic schemas; return domain results or raise domain exceptions.
- Enqueue background jobs from here, not from routers.

## Repositories

- Persistence only — queries and mapping to/from models.
- One repository per aggregate or bounded context when the codebase uses that pattern.
